text:
Repeated visit for their BBQ dishes. Would usually order their leather jacket grilled fish and their stir fry Kai Lan.

Love that dried shrimps are added in the stir fry Kai Lan elevating that umami-ness.

Ordered their sambal sotong - excellent doneness; sotong not overly cooked, nice bite to it.

Love their chinchalok which compliments the sambal seafood.
Sambal stingray medium $18 excluding rice - sambal lacks intensity and spice, stingray meat portion is sizable but overcooked. Average at best.
$18 sambal stingray. Sauce tastes more like tomato sauce than sambal.

Uncle was friendly and sent the order to our table. Unfortunately, the food was rather disappointing. The belachan of the stingray was too sweet, and tasted like it contained ketchup. The kangkong was well fried but was extremely salty. Everything served in disposables.
The uncle is stern as he needs to take orders, collect money, serves the food... hence he is playing many roles. Repeated visit for their delicious sambal sotong!
